<paragraph blockId="141.[151,1437,1637,2025]" lastBlockId="142.[151,1437,152,503]" lastPageId="142" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1818,1844]" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marenzeller" box="[325,536,1818,1844]" firstAuthor="Marenzeller" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="64 - 66" refId="ref189523" refString="Marenzeller, E. von (1892) Note preliminaire sur les Holothuries provenant des campagnes du yacht l'Hirondelle. Bulletin Societe Zoologique France, 17, 64 - 66." type="journal article" year="1892">Marenzeller (1892</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marenzeller" box="[547,604,1818,1844]" firstAuthor="Marenzeller" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref189554" refString="Marenzeller, E. von (1893) Contribution a l'etude des Holothuries de l'Atlantique N'ord (Golfe de Gascogne, Iles Acores). Resultats Campagnes Scientifiques du Prince de Monaco, 6, 1 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11304" type="journal article" year="1893">1893</bibRefCitation>
) described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="$ Marenzeller" authorityYear="1892" box="[734,972,1818,1844]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="janthina">
<emphasis box="[734,972,1818,1844]" italics="true" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Benthodytes janthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a single specimen collected by 
<emphasis box="[151,272,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Hirondelle</emphasis>
, roughly 
<quantity box="[384,496,1854,1880]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5749504" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" unit="mi" value="160.0">160 miles</quantity>
north of Terceira 
<collectingCountry box="[706,778,1854,1880]" name="Iceland" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Island</collectingCountry>
. The specimen lacked complete information on important diagnostic characters, such as the ossicles that were broken and partially dissolved. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="$ Marenzeller" authorityYear="1892" box="[1259,1384,1890,1916]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="janthina">
<emphasis box="[1259,1384,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">B. janthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was later recorded from several localities in the NE Atlantic, from 
<collectingCountry box="[854,971,1926,1952]" name="Greenland" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Greenland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Heding" box="[986,1135,1926,1952]" firstAuthor="Heding" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref183688" refString="Heding, S. G. (1942) Holothurioidea, Part 2: Aspidochirota, Elasipoda, Dendrochirota. In: The Danish Ingolf Expedition. 4 (13). Hagerup, Copenhagen, pp. 1 - 39." type="book chapter" year="1942">Heding 1942</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[1180,1313,1926,1952]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Herouard" firstAuthor="Herouard" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="1 - 161" refId="ref184267" refString="Herouard, E. (1923) Holothuries provenant des campagnes des yachts Princesse-Alice et Hirondelle ii. (1898 - 1915). Resultats Campagnes Scientifiques Prince de Monaco, 66, 1 - 161." type="journal article" year="1923">Hérouard 1923</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Herouard" box="[232,420,1962,1988]" firstAuthor="Herouard" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="1 - 62" refId="ref184203" refString="Herouard, E. (1902) Holothuries Provenant Des Campagnes De La Princesse-Alice (1892 - 1897). Reisultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht, Fasc. 21, 1 - 62." type="book chapter" year="1902">Hérouard (1902)</bibRefCitation>
attempted to complete Marenzeller’s initial description based on individuals collected by 
<emphasis box="[151,325,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Princesse Alice</emphasis>
, which included material dredge within Azorean waters (sta 673: 
<geoCoordinate box="[1067,1206,1997,2024]" degrees="37" direction="north" minutes="51" orientation="latitude" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" precision="15" seconds="00" value="37.85">37°51’00”N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1218,1362,1997,2024]" degrees="26" direction="west" minutes="53" orientation="longitude" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" precision="15" seconds="45" value="-26.895834">26°53’45”W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity lastPageId="142" lastPageNumber="143" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.252" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" unit="m" value="2.252">2,252 m</quantity>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" box="[196,362,152,179]" firstAuthor="Hansen" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref183443" refString="Hansen, B. (1975) Systematics and biology of the deep-sea holothurians: Elasipoda. Galathea report: scientific results of the Danish deep-sea expedition round the world 1950 - 1952. Galathea, 13, 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1975">Hansen (1975)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed these reports and concluded that they resulted from confusion with other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" box="[1299,1436,153,179]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Benthodytes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" box="[339,440,190,215]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="typica">
<emphasis box="[339,440,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B. typica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As a result, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="$ Marenzeller" authorityYear="1892" box="[594,719,189,215]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="janthina">
<emphasis box="[594,611,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[626,719,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">janthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was again reduced to the type specimen. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" firstAuthor="Hansen" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref183443" refString="Hansen, B. (1975) Systematics and biology of the deep-sea holothurians: Elasipoda. Galathea report: scientific results of the Danish deep-sea expedition round the world 1950 - 1952. Galathea, 13, 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1975">Hansen (1975)</bibRefCitation>
commented that due to the poor preservation state of the 
<typeStatus box="[872,970,225,251]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">holotype</typeStatus>
it was not possible to review the species’ status and its affinities. On studying deep-sea material from the Porcupine Abyssal Plain (SW 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1269,261,288]" name="Ireland" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Ireland</collectingCountry>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Billett" box="[1286,1436,261,287]" firstAuthor="Billett" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" refId="ref173746" refString="Billett, D. S. M. (1988) The ecology of deep-sea holothurians. PhD thesis (unpublished), University of Southampton, Southampton, xi + 398 pp." type="book" year="1988">Billett (1988)</bibRefCitation>
believed that both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="$ Marenzeller" authorityYear="1892" box="[364,490,297,323]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="janthina">
<emphasis box="[364,381,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[397,490,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">janthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Perrier, 1896 b" authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1896" box="[549,825,297,323]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lingua">
<emphasis box="[549,566,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[582,654,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">lingua</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Perrier" box="[663,825,297,323]" firstAuthor="Perrier" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="900 - 903" refId="ref197343" refString="Perrier, R. (1896 b) Sur les Elasipodes recueillis par le Travailleur et le Talisman. Comptes Rendus Academie Sciences, Paris, 123, 900 - 903." type="journal article" year="1896" yearSuffix="b">Perrier, 1896b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were junior synonyms of the Indo-Pacific 
<taxonomicName authority="Theel, 1882" authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="sordida">
<emphasis box="[1318,1335,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1351,1437,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">sordida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Theel" box="[151,290,333,359]" firstAuthor="Theel" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref201995" refString="Theel, H. (1882) Report on the Holothuroidea dredged by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Part I. Challenger Reports, Zoology, 4, 1 - 176." type="journal article" year="1882">Théel, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, dismissing many of the diagnostic characters as individual variation or a result of the preservation process (
<emphasis box="[256,302,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">e.g.,</emphasis>
shrinkage and retraction, loss of colour, absence of ossicles). Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rogacheva" box="[1155,1436,369,395]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rogacheva" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="460 - 478" refId="ref198877" refString="Rogacheva, A., Cross, I. A. &amp; Billett, D. S. M. (2009) Psychropotid holothurians (Echinodermata: Holothuroidea: Elasipodida) collected at abyssal depths from around the Crozet Plateau in the southern Indian Ocean. Zootaxa, 2096, 460 - 478." type="journal article" year="2009">
Rogacheva 
<emphasis box="[1291,1344,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" box="[282,401,405,431]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="sordida">
<emphasis box="[282,299,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[315,401,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">sordida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be conspecific with Indo-Pacific 
<taxonomicName authority="Theel, 1882" authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" box="[820,1120,405,431]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Chiridotidae" genus="Chiridota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="abyssicola">
<emphasis box="[820,971,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B. abyssicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Theel" box="[981,1120,405,431]" firstAuthor="Theel" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref201995" refString="Theel, H. (1882) Report on the Holothuroidea dredged by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Part I. Challenger Reports, Zoology, 4, 1 - 176." type="journal article" year="1882">Théel, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and dismissed the Atlantic records as misidentifications. The matter whether Azorean 
<taxonomicName authorityName="$ Marenzeller" authorityYear="1892" box="[801,924,441,467]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="janthina">
<emphasis box="[801,924,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B. janthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with other Atlantic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" box="[1299,1436,441,467]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Benthodytes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1896" box="[248,351,477,503]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae" genus="Benthodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Elasipodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lingua">
<emphasis box="[248,351,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B. lingua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?) or indeed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" box="[492,641,477,503]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Chiridotidae" genus="Chiridota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="abyssicola">
<emphasis box="[492,641,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">B. abyssicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is still pending on future revisions of the genus.
</paragraph>
